properties.areaDesc: Orange County Coastal; San Diego County Coastal Areas
properties.headline: High Surf Advisory issued January 24 at 5:34AM PST until January 26 at 6:00PM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
...HIGH SURF ALONG THE COAST THIS WEEKEND...

Long period west-northwest swell from 285 degrees will generate
high surf at area beaches tonight through Sunday afternoon. Surf
will peak Saturday, with highest surf 5 to 8 feet in San Diego
County. Locally high surf also likely in Orange County up to 7
feet. Surf subsiding late Sunday.

* Waves and Surf...5 to 8 feet in San Diego County, and 5 to 7
feet in Orange County.

* Timing...Late Friday night through Sunday, with highest surf
Saturday.

* Tides...La Jolla high tide Saturday of 5.8 feet at 852 AM,
followed by a low tide of -0.9 feet at 359 PM.

* Impacts...Dangerous swimming conditions and a high risk of rip
currents. Local beach erosion possible. Always swim near a
lifeguard!
properties.instruction:
A High Surf Advisory means that high surf will affect beaches in
the advisory area...producing localized beach erosion and
dangerous swimming conditions.
